HOUSE RESOLUTION NO. 399
BY REPRESENTATIVE MCMAKIN
A RESOLUTION
To commend the Louisiana Blazers Elite youth softball team on winning the 2026 USA
Softball 16u National Championship.
WHEREAS, Louisiana Blazers Elite is a youth softball organization that coaches
young women to play high-level softball; the organization begins at 8u and has teams up to
18u Amateur; the 16u and 18u teams focus primarily on team and individual player
development while also improving players who strive to play in college; and
WHEREAS, the Louisiana Blazers Elite 16u team competed in Oklahoma City
during the summer of 2025; the team played at Devon Park, the home of the Women's
College World Series, and brought home the USA Softball 16u National Championship; and
WHEREAS, the Louisiana Blazers Elite 16u team is the first Louisiana team to win
the tournament in any age group; the team was undefeated in eleven games, scored fifty-
eight runs, and allowed only eight runs; the team shutout its opponents in the quarterfinals,
semifinals, and championship games; and
WHEREAS, the Louisiana Blazers Elite youth softball team is coached by Will
Spencer, JC Fressina, and Logan Lewis; and
WHEREAS, the members of the Louisiana Blazers Elite are Jeanne Janise, Harper
Fresina, Riley Williams, Kodi Ricks, McKenzie Creel, Riley Perilloux, Bailey Spencer,
Bailey Ducote, Avery Hastings, A K Phillips, Rae'El Wheat, Karli Williams, and Aubrey
Gaudet; and
WHEREAS, the Louisiana Blazers Elite 16u softball team and the entire organization
are most deserving of recognition for their outstanding achievement.
